cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.MM

This paper is primarily focused on the design of access reservation protocols for Internet of Things (IoT) applications in 5G networks. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper involves optimization techniques and analysis of algorithms, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also deals with system-level issues such as scalability and resource consumption, which could place it in the cs.SY (Systems and Control) category. Finally, the paper involves simulations and performance evaluation, which could also make it relevant to the cs.MM (Multimedia) category.
